The paper deals with achievable rates in typical random number generation problems, which are closely related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses mixed sources, which can be seen as a type of data structure (cs.DS). The paper also touches on fixed-length source coding, which is a subfield of cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses extensions to more general mixed sources, which could fall under machine learning (cs.MM) or statistical learning (cs.LG).
